62.1	Revenge	Revenge	Revenge is a harmful action against a person or group in response to a grievance, be it real or perceived. It is also called payback, retribution, retaliation or vengeance; it may be characterized as a form of justice, an altruistic action which enforces societal rules and which is based on a deep rooted evolutionary instinct that helped humanity by implementing social cohesion in a subtle way.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/DVinfernoMegaeraTisifphoneAlecto_m.jpg/160px-DVinfernoMegaeraTisifphoneAlecto_m.jpg
